First Citizens BancShares, Inc. Key Developments

First Citizens BancShares Declares Quarterly Dividend, Payable on October 2, 2017
Jul 26 17
The Board of Directors of First Citizens BancShares Inc. declared on July 25, 2017, a quarterly dividend of 30 cents per share on the Class A and Class B common stock. The dividend is payable on October 2, 2017, to shareholders of record September 18, 2017.


First Citizens BancShares Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Financial Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017; Announces Net Charge-Offs on Total Loans and Leases for the Second Quarter Ended June 30, 2017
Jul 26 17
First Citizens BancShares Inc. announced unaudited consolidated financial results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, net interest income was $261,609,000 compared to $232,189,000 a year ago. Income before income taxes was $211,879,000 compared to $109,574,000 a year ago. Net income was $134,660,000 or $11.21 per share compared to $69,316,000 or $5.77 per share a year ago. Annualized return on average assets was 1.58% compared to 0.87% a year ago. Annualized return on average equity was 17.10% compared to 9.33% a year ago. The increase in net interest income was due to higher non-PCI loan interest income of $8.0 million, a $1.9 million increase in interest income earned on overnight investments, an increase in PCI loan interest income of $1.1 million and higher investment securities interest income of $655,000. These increases were partially offset by an increase in interest expense of $419,000 primarily related to higher rates paid on short-term borrowings.

For the six months, net interest income was $511,952,000 compared to $464,909,000 a year ago. Income before income taxes was $316,938,000 compared to $191,062,000 a year ago. Net income was $202,281,000 or $16.84 per share compared to $121,388,000 or $10.11 per share a year ago. Annualized return on average assets was 1.20% compared to 0.76% a year ago. Annualized return on average equity was 13.11% compared to 8.26% a year ago. Book value per share at period-end was $269.75 against $252.76 a year ago. 

Net charge-offs on total loans and leases were $4.5 million, or 0.08% of average loans and leases on an annualized basis, compared to $6.1 million, or 0.11%, during the first quarter of 2017.


First Citizens BancShares, Inc. Declares Quarterly Dividend on Class A and Class B Common Stock, Payable on July 5, 2017
Apr 26 17
The Board of Directors of First Citizens BancShares Inc. declared on April 25, 2017, a quarterly dividend of 30 cents per share on the Class A and Class B common stock. The dividend is payable July 5, 2017, to shareholders of record June 27, 2017.


