1994 - acquired The Bank of Bladenboro in Bladenboro, North Carolina, Edgecomb Homestead Savings Bank of Tarboro, North Carolina, and First Republic Savings Bank FSB of Roanoke Rapids, North Carolina[17]
1995 - acquired First Investors Savings Bank of Whiteville, North Carolina and State Bank of Fayetteville, North Carolina[17]
1996 - acquired First-Citizens Bank & Trust Company of Lawrenceville, Virginia, Peoples Savings Bank of Wilmington, North Carolina, and Summit Savings Bank of Sanford, North Carolina[17]
1997 - acquired First Savings Bank of Rockingham County in Reidsville, North Carolina[17]
1998 - acquired First Citizens Bank & Trust Company of White Sulphur Springs, West Virginia[17]
2003 - acquired Avery County Bank of Newland, North Carolina[17]
2009 - U.S. Bank National Association, a subsidiary bank of U.S. Bancorp, entered into a definitive agreement to purchase the bond trustee business of First Citizens Bank, a subsidiary of First Citizens BancShares.
2009 - acquired Temecula Valley Bank[20] of Temecula, California and Venture Bank[21] of Lacey, Washington
2010 - acquired First Regional Bank of Los Angeles, California[17] and Sun American Bank of Boca Raton, Florida[17]
2011 - changed Ironstone Bank to division from subsidiary[6]
2011 - acquired United Western Bank of Denver, Colorado[7]
2011 - acquired Colorado Capital Bank of Castle Rock, Colorado[8]
2013 - announced merger with 1st Financial Corp. of Hendersonville, North Carolina
2014 - announced merger with First Citizens Bank of South Carolina
2015 - acquired Capitol City Bank and Trust Company of Atlanta, Georgia [22]

