 About Us Menu
Who We Are

Working hard. Asking questions. Planning ahead. Taking care of customers.Forever First®.
For more than 100 years, customers have trusted First Citizens Bank with
    their money … and their futures. And that's a trust we've taken
    seriously every day we've been in business. For every First Citizens
    customer, now or in the future, we make a simple promise: We will always
    live and work by the values that have distinguished First Citizens since the
    day we opened our doors.


    Forever First is our commitment to the people, businesses and communities
    who rely on us to be the best we can be. As we say in our advertising,
    "Money isn't everything. But so much depends on what you do with your money."


    First Citizens Bank. Forever First®.

Corporate Profile

	First-Citizens Bank & Trust Company is a North Carolina state-chartered commercial 
	bank headquartered in Raleigh, North Carolina. It is a wholly owned subsidiary of 
	First Citizens BancShares, Inc. (NASDAQ: FCNCA/FCNCB), a Delaware financial holding
	company also headquartered in Raleigh. Get an overview of First Citizens, a company
	that has grown to more than $31 billion in assets.



Our Values

    Through the years, we’ve grown our company on the kind of fundamental values
    that never go out of style:  Working hard, working with integrity, listening
    to what our customers have to say and taking the long term view.  We don’t
    chase short-term fads and gimmicks; instead, we believe in making sound
    decisions that create real security and growth for years — and generations
    — yet to come.



Diversity

    We’re committed to reflecting the rich diversity of the communities where we
    live and do business. We strive to enable and encourage all our associates
    to achieve their full potential by contributing to business success and
    service excellence.



 Privacy and Security

    No matter how you choose to bank with First Citizens, the security of your
    financial information is among our highest priorities. Take steps to protect
    yourself online and off.



 First Citizens Bank Social Media Terms of Use

    We welcome you to join the conversation, to share your experiences, and connect. 
    View our terms and conditions to answer your questions about engaging with 
    First Citizens Bank through any of our social media platforms.



 Corporate Governance

    Our corporate governance practices reflect the high ethical principles that
    guide us at every level. We make our Code of Ethics, Bylaws and Corporate
    Governance Guidelines available for your review so that you can see how we
    define our business practices.



 Annual Report Summary

    Review the Chairman's Letter to Shareholders, the Annual Report on Form 10-K
    and Proxy Statement.



 Interactive Data Files
XBRL files are provided for use in your XBRL rendering or analytical software.

 IRS Form 8937
Access First Citizens BancShares' Report of Organizational Actions Affecting Basis of Securities (IRS Form 8937).

 Registrar and Transfer Agent
    Information on contacting our registrar and Transfer Agent, Broadridge
    Corporate Issuer Solutions, Inc., for shareholder inquiries/instructions
    related to BancShares stock.



